        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3451555624" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3588008124600878378">I enjoyed this book much more than <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/37380.The_Heart_Is_a_Lonely_Hunter' title='The Heart Is a Lonely Hunter by Carson McCullers' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Heart Is a Lonely Hunter</a> which I gave five stars to and this book, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/330244.The_Member_of_the_Wedding' title='The Member of the Wedding by Carson McCullers' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Member of the Wedding</a> I only gave four stars.<br/><br/>Let me start by saying that I absolutely love books that are set in this time period in the south, so that was a plus right out of the gate! The main character, Frankie, was, to me anyway, slightly touched in the head. Crazy, somewhat deranged. Goodread members described her as having “growing pains”. Either way, she definitely had issues! <br/><br/>My </span>
  <span id="freeText3588008124600878378" style="display:none">I enjoyed this book much more than <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/37380.The_Heart_Is_a_Lonely_Hunter" title="The Heart Is a Lonely Hunter by Carson McCullers" rel="nofollow noopener">The Heart Is a Lonely Hunter</a> which I gave five stars to and this book, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/330244.The_Member_of_the_Wedding" title="The Member of the Wedding by Carson McCullers" rel="nofollow noopener">The Member of the Wedding</a> I only gave four stars.<br /><br />Let me start by saying that I absolutely love books that are set in this time period in the south, so that was a plus right out of the gate! The main character, Frankie, was, to me anyway, slightly touched in the head. Crazy, somewhat deranged. Goodread members described her as having “growing pains”. Either way, she definitely had issues! <br /><br />My four star rating is based on the ending. The book was going on quite nicely but once I got to the end I felt cheated. It seemed very rushed to me like <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3506.Carson_McCullers" title="Carson McCullers" rel="nofollow noopener">Carson McCullers</a> didn’t know how to end it. <br /><br />It’s worth the read because McCullers can (could) write.<br /><br /></span>
